\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. S. indicus} (L.) R. Br.,{\i  Prodr. Fl. Nov. Holl.} 170 (1810). Stems 60-100 cm, erect, in large clumps with numerous leafy shoots at base. Cauline leaves few, 20-30 cm, long-attenuate, flat or folded, aculeolate on margins and upper surface. Panicle up to 30 cm, linear-cylindrical, stiff, dark greyish, often more open and lax at base. Spikelets 1·5-2·5 mm, crowded on slender, erect, usually appressed branches; glumes unequal, the lower obtuse, the upper acute, half as long as the acute lemma; lemma longer than the obtuse palea. Anthers 0·5 mm. 2n = 36.{\i  Waste places and roadsides. Naturalized in S. Europe.} [Az Bu Ga Hs It Lu.] ({\i Tropics and subtropics}.)
\par

