\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. C. alopecuroides} (Piller & Mitterp.) Schrader, {\i Fl. Germ.} 167 (1806) ({\i Heleochloa alopecuroides} (Piller & Mitterp.) Host ex Roemer). Stems up to 30 cm, numerous, geniculately ascending. Leaves green or somewhat glaucous, shortly hairy above; sheaths glabrous, the uppermost longer than lamina, scarcely inflated. Inflorescence up to 8 × 0·8 cm. Spikelets 2-3 mm, shortly pedicellate. Glumes lanceolate, ciliate-serrulate on the keel. Lemma little longer than glumes, but exserted. Stamens 3.{\i  Seasonally wet places. Europe northwards to N.C. France, Czechoslovakia and C. Russia.} ?Al Au Bu Co Cz Ga Gr Hu It Ju Lu Rm Rs (C, W, K, E) Si Tu.
